annotationA: LD28793p; GTPase activity; translation elongation factor activity; GTP binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: translational elongation; positive regulation of Ras protein signal transduction; positive regulation of ERK1 and ERK2 cascade; mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
annotationB: Elongation factor 1-gamma; Ef1gamma associates with other EF1 subunits (alpha/beta/delta). It binds tubulin and Doa protein kinase, which in turns phosphorylates Ef1gamma. Ef1gamma regulates organelle movement along microtubules
